        h2#terminology Terminology
        dl
          dt Flight path
          dd The path through space traced by the centre of gravity

          dt Equivalent airspeed (EAS)
          dd The airspeed at sea level in the International Standard Atmosphere at which the dynamic pressure is the same as the dynamic pressure at the true airspeed (TAS) and altitude at which the aircraft is flying.
          dd \[ \frac{1}{2} \rho V^2 = \frac{1}{2} \rho_0 V_E^2 \]
          dd \[ V = V_E \left(\frac{\rho_0}{\rho}\right)^\frac{1}{2} = \frac{V_E}{\sqrt{\sigma}} \]
        h3#wing-planform-terminology Wing planform terminology
        dl
          dt Chord
          dd The distance between the leading edge and the trailing edge

          dt Taper ratio
          dd The ratio between the tip chord and the root chord
          dd \[ \lambda = \frac{c_T}{c_R} \] 

          dt Wing sweep
          dd The angle that the wing makes against oncoming flow

          dt Aspect ratio
          dd Non-tapered wings: ratio between the wing span and the mean chord
          dd \[ A = \frac{b}{\bar{c}} \]
          dd Tapered wings: ratio between the wing span and the planform area
          dd \[ A = \frac{b^2}{S} \]



